23/01/2011
ANKARA, Turkey -- Police detained a Saudi on Friday (January 21st) wanted for suspected links to the al-Qaida terrorist network.
The man, identified by the initials WB, was arrested in the southern city of Adana, along with a Turkish national, after police received a tip that an extremist was planning an act of violence in the city.
The man is wanted by Saudi Arabia on terror-related charges.
(AFP, Anadolu news agency, The Saudi Gazette - 21/01/11)
